snippet.textDisplay: When I read the title I knew what this song would be about. A survivor and recovering victim of gaslighting. Now learning boundaries, who to surround myself with and to be aware when my trauma appears, and to not always feel like I’m in the wrong or only I can’t do something when I can. I took child and youth care but didn’t finish, only because they taught you want you needed to know and then the policies. This helped to know who really wanted to complete it. Which is smart. I was doing great but I needed to be doing something else. I did this course mainly to help me and those who are close to me around me. Getting mental health is hard atm but I hope that it gets better. Never had an issue with strangers or friends who just like anyone. Has a past but their behaviour doesn’t impact your life ( you being the opposite person); vice versa. Also podcasts help. Thanks for making this song. I’ll have to take my sister to one of their concerts. She’s a huge fan.
